class datasets.LibSvmDataset(givenFnPath, givenNumberOfSamples, givenNumberOfFeatures)[source]¶

Dataset is represented like the LIBSVM dataset. Every sample and its label looks like: \([\mathbf{y}, \mathbf{x_1}, \mathbf{x_2}, \mathbf{x_3}]\). There is NO header, and the first column, i.e. \(\mathbf{y}\), represents label.

all samples. numberOfSamples by numberOfFeatures

class datasets.StructureMedicalDatasets(givenFnPath, givenNumberOfSamples, givenNumberOfFeatures)[source]¶

Every sample and its label looks like: \([\mathbf{y}, \mathbf{x1}, \mathbf{x2}, \mathbf{x3}]\). There HAS header, and the first column, i.e. \(\mathbf{y}\), represents label. When conducting binary classification, labels include ‘-1’ and ‘1’.
